We will run the command 
-$ ifconfig #to check what ip is allocated to the linux machine and also the subnet.

2nd Command.
-$ nmap -sn 192.168.56.1/24 # We are trying to see which IP our machine has been allocated to  in the subnet and if the host is up.

3rd Command.
-$ nmap -p 0-65000 -A 192.168.56.15 #scans all ports from  0- 65000. "-A" flag is for aggressive mode that bundles multiple flags.
